  "prompt": "How much refund will I get on my PRS counter ticket if my seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train? Can I board the train using it",
  "response": "If your Passenger Reservation System (PRS) ticket remains waitlisted even after the train has departed, here\u2019s what typically happens regarding refunds and boarding privileges:\n\n### **Refund Eligibility**\n\n1. **Waitlisted Tickets at Departure:**\n   - **Unconfirmed Status:** If your ticket remains in the waitlist (WL) category even after the train has left the station, it means your reservation was not confirmed, and you did not travel.\n   - **Refund Claim:** In such cases, you are generally **eligible for a full refund** of the ticket fare since the service was not rendered. However, this is subject to the specific railway\u2019s refund policies.\n\n2. **Cancellation Fees:**\n   - **Before Departure:** If you cancel a waitlisted ticket before the train departs or before the chart is prepared (usually a few hours before departure), there might be a nominal cancellation fee deducted from your refund.\n   - **After Departure:** If you realize post-departure that your ticket was still waitlisted and did not travel, you should immediately initiate a refund request as per the railway\u2019s guidelines. Typically, more significant refunds are possible if no journey occurred.\n\n3. **How to Claim Refund:**\n   - **Online Bookings:** If you booked online (e.g., through the railway\u2019s official website or authorized apps), you can request a refund through the same platform.\n   - **PRS Counter Tickets:** For tickets purchased at a PRS counter, visit the same counter or the designated refund center with your ticket and identification to process the refund.\n\n### **Boarding the Train**\n\n- **Waitlisted Status:** If your ticket remains waitlisted after the train's departure, it indicates that your reservation was not confirmed. Consequently, **you are not permitted to board the train** using that ticket.\n  \n- **No RAC or Confirmation:** Without a Reservation Against Cancellation (RAC) status or a confirmed seat, there\u2019s no official allocation for you to board the train safely.\n\n### **Recommendations**\n\n1. **Check Ticket Status:** Always verify your ticket status online before the journey to ensure whether it's confirmed, RAC, or waitlisted.\n   \n2. **Early Reservation:** To minimize the chances of ending up with a waitlisted ticket, try to book your tickets well in advance, especially during peak travel seasons.\n\n3. **Alternative Plans:** If you find your ticket is still waitlisted close to departure, consider making alternative travel arrangements to avoid inconvenience.\n\n4. **Contact Customer Service:** If you face issues with refunds or have specific questions about your ticket, reaching out to the railway's customer service can provide personalized assistance.\n\n### **Summary**\n\n- **Refund:** Generally available for waitlisted tickets not confirmed by departure, minus any applicable fees.\n- **Boarding:** Not allowed if your ticket remains waitlisted after the train has departed.\n\nAlways refer to the specific railway\u2019s official refund policies or contact their customer support for detailed and accurate information tailored to your situation.",
